ENTRY       EC 1.14.11.40               Enzyme
NAME        enduracididine beta-hydroxylase;
            MppO
CLASS       Oxidoreductases;
            Acting on paired donors, with incorporation or reduction of molecular oxygen;
            With 2-oxoglutarate as one donor, and incorporation of one atom of oxygen into each donor
SYSNAME     L-enduracididine,2-oxoglutarate:O2 oxidoreductase (3-hydroxylating)
REACTION    L-enduracididine + 2-oxoglutarate + O2 = (3S)-3-hydroxy-L-enduracididine + succinate + CO2 [RN:R10413]
ALL_REAC    R10413
SUBSTRATE   L-enduracididine [CPD:C20602];
            2-oxoglutarate [CPD:C00026];
            O2 [CPD:C00007]
PRODUCT     (3S)-3-hydroxy-L-enduracididine [CPD:C20603];
            succinate [CPD:C00042];
            CO2 [CPD:C00011]
COMMENT     Fe2+-dependent enzyme. The enzyme is involved in biosynthesis of the nonproteinogenic amino acid beta-hydroxyenduracididine, a component of the mannopeptimycins (cyclic glycopeptide antibiotic), produced by Streptomyces hygroscopicus NRRL 30439.
